<AnyLogicWorkspace WorkspaceVersion="1.9" AnyLogicVersion="8.9.7.qualifier" AlpVersion="8.9.7">
<Model>
	<Id>1374576348666</Id>
	<Name><![CDATA[Shopping Mall]]></Name>
	<Description><![CDATA[This is a model of a hypothetical Shopping Mall with over a hundred shops (including several anchor shops), a movie theater, a food court, and a skating ring. AnyLogic Pedestrian Library is used throughout the model. The mall has multiple entrances with stairs and escalators. The mall visitors are assigned randomly generated task lists and follow their task sequences while in the mall. 
Activity of a visitor while in a shop is modeled as a stochastic delay – this is a good assumption as we are concentrating on densities and possible congestions. You can view the density map of the main shopping level of mall. When the mall closes (that happens in 10 hours after the model starts or if you press the “Close Mall” button), all visitors proceed to the exits and leave the mall; you can then reopen the mall. 
This is a good starting point for further enhancements: you can experiment with different arrival rates, add a parking at the lower level,modify the visitor behavior (e.g., make it dependent on what they see while walking), etc.]]></Description>
	<EngineVersion>6</EngineVersion>
	<JavaPackageName><![CDATA[shopping_mall]]></JavaPackageName>
	<ModelTimeUnit><![CDATA[Minute]]></ModelTimeUnit>
